         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[Roma] ¶ 2nd April 1879 ¶ Baron Von Müller ¶ Melbourne ¶ Dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.04.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Singleton</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Trema tomentosa</seg> (MEL 2215720).</p>
               </note>[Roma]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The writing is unclear and M evidently had difficulty deciphering it, for there is an annotation by him: 'Moma [<seg style="font-style: italic; ">deleted</seg>], Q.L. Ruma or Roma'. A George Lewis Singleton was managing a pastoral property at Roma at this time.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2nd April 1879</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Under separate cover I send you sample of leaf and seeds of a plant or shrub found in this neighbourhood —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is only found in thick scrubs or deep well sheltered gullies grows to the height of from five to eight feet, and cannot stand frost from the effects of which withers like a young orange.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would feel very thankfull if you could kindly inform me if it is poisonous as last winter we found four head of young cattle dead in its immediate vicinity.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. L. Singleton</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
